.TH OPENMERC 1 "$(date +%Y-%m-%d)" "openmerc 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
openmerc \- diffusion‑powered LLM terminal UI
.SH SYNOPSIS
openmerc [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
openmerc is a terminal UI for interacting with a diffusion‑powered language model. By default it launches the interactive UI. It can also run in headless mode or initialise a configuration file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h, --help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.BR -V, --version
Show version information and exit.
.TP
.BR --headless " "PROMPT
Run in headless mode, feeding the given PROMPT to the model and printing the result.
.TP
.BR --init
Create a default .openmerc.toml configuration file in the current directory.
.TP
.BR --session " "NAME
Resume a previously saved session with the given NAME.
.SH EXAMPLES
.B Launch UI:
.n
openmerc

.B Headless mode:
.n
openmerc --headless "Explain quantum computing"

.B Initialise config:
.n
openmerc --init

.B Resume session:
.n
openmerc --session "my‑project"
